<br>
To start with, the Romans should have had everything they needed for a balloon flight.  They had a canvas, designed to keep heat in.  They had baskets, fire, an understanding that fire could make light objects rise. And certainly its military commanders would have felt a burning need to be able to see from higher ground than the opposing commanders could, whatever was happening in the field.  Still, so far as we know, it never happened.  <br>
<br>
A heliograph system should have been easy for the Romans.  They had codes, organization…everything they should have needed to set up a series of heliograph towers, that could have sent messages across the empire in a day.  As opposed to the weeks, it took messages by horse carrier.  Still it never happened.   <br>
<br>
Ahh the foundation series was a masterpiece.  Well the first 3 books were anyway.  Foundation, Foundation and Empire, and Second Foundation.  For some reason, Asimov did all his very best writing as a youth.  Something happened when he went back in his old age to attempt to write more foundation stuff.  It was all pretty dreadful.  I wish he had just left it as the trilogy.  <br>
